cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about a neural network model for abstractive summarization, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The model also uses reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the model involves attention mechanisms and sequence prediction, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance on text datasets, which is relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
